      "source": "memory",
      "snippet": "Mistake: Used Batch Script Instead of Subagents for Product Image Generation: Context: User asked to generate first images for all selected 商品表 products and explicitly said to use the skill.; Trigger: I implemented the work with a resumable batch script in the main session.; Correction: User angrily clarified that the intended execution model was to dispatch subagents, one product per subagent, not to write a batch script.; Lesson: For multi-product ecommerce image generation, the user expects subagent orchestration. Do not substitute a batch script for the main execution path, even if a script seems more controllable or resumable.",
